
Gwangalli Beach was beautiful, stunning clean white sand and views over the ocean but the esplanade and surrounding streets are tourist traps, very commercial and unappealing that we couldn't wait to get away from the area.
Nice beach and view of the bridge. Some good food options, some not.
Fun drone show on Saturday eve and watching the boats square up and shoot fireworks was fun.
Visiting Gwangalli Beach in Busan was an unforgettable experience, with its stunning ocean views and vibrant atmosphere. The highlight was seeing the illuminated Gwangan Bridge at night, reflecting beautifully on the water. I enjoyed walking along the sandy shore, feeling the cool sea breeze while watching street performances and lively crowds. The area was filled with cozy cafes and seafood restaurants, making it a perfect spot to relax and enjoy fresh local cuisine. Whether day or night, Gwangalli Beach offered a perfect blend of relaxation and excitement, making my trip truly memorable.
We were staying in Songdo, which is quiet and relaxing, so we thought we would come for the day. Cheap Taxi ride to the beach, which was extremely busy. Had a good look around the shops etc. There are so many food places it is unreal. We went primarily on Saturday night to see the drone show, which was epic. To showings, 8pm and 10pm. We enjoyed the show from a great little spot called Cococ. They have an upstairs as well as downstairs  area, great food, and cool atmosphere.
The drone show was spectacular, and I loved it. This is a must do if you are around on a Saturday night.
여름밤에 해수욕장 특히 주말 밤은 해변에 정말 사람이 많은거 같음..
밤에는 차없는 거리도 되고 토요일 밤 8시 10시 드론쇼도 있어서 사람들이 정말 많음.. 연인들이 오면 정말 좋은 장소인거 같음...
