A great family activity! The cruise over in the cable car gave sweeping views of the city. The songdo park had lots to explore and we could have spent many more hours there going on one of the hikes. We enjoyed all of the photo ops on the roof of the cable car building and recommend spending the small fee to head out to the suspension bridge/island.
This is an amazing cable car ride with overwhelming views of the Busan bay and city. We took the clear bottom car which was a bit scary but still amazing. It takes about 10 minutes each way and we found that one way trip was enough.
The cable car is called "Busan Air Cruise," which connects Songdo Beach to Songdo Sky Park. It is a popular tourist attraction, so there can be a line. There are  food stalls at the Sky Park station. Side note that most of the signs and literature are not in English. It was a pleasant ride and the stunning views. On arrival we walked around, the lines for food were really long. We did the sky walk then left.
Beautiful views and an enjoyable ride. There are some lovely walks at the other end which provide awesome views. Some of the tracks are very steep. Reasonable price to ride and we'll worth a visit.
