주차장 넓음, 상영10분전에 도착해야함. 여기는 영화가 광고없이 바로 진행됨.  매점 정보가 없어서 센텀에서 샌드위치 사서 왔는에 편의점에 팝콘,빵 음료등이 다양하게 판매되고있음. (단 냄새나는 핫도그나 이런건 영화관내에서 먹을수없음)
스크린도 크고 좌석도 편함. 무엇보다 사람이 붐비지않아서 원하는 영화를 여유있게 볼수있음.

We had wanted to stay in this lovely boutique hotel since booking for 2020 but unfortunately had to cancel due to Covid.  Fast track to 2025 and the opportunity arose again so we booked the Junior Suite with views up and down Madison Avenue and East 41st Street.  Everything about the hotel was perfect except for one thing – the building was shrouded in scaffolding, denying us a clear view.  In hindsight, we wish the management had of notified us regarding this issue before arriving but at the same time we understood the reason for the construction. Despite the disappointment, the hotel was absolutely charming, and our room beautiful, well-appointed and spacious.  The staff were very helpful, attentive and accommodating to all our needs and we appreciated their efforts to locate a taxi for us during the “rally day”.  The well stocked complimentary snack room was a major plus, as were all the wonderful books, and the rooftop bar looked amazing, although the night we went up it was closed for a private function. We could not have picked a more centralised, cosy and quiet hotel for our first visit to NYC and look forward to returning in the future, hopefully with a clearer view next time. Highly recommended!
Still my favorite hotel in NYC. I've stayed there so often if feels like home to me now. Comfort is what I feel the minute I walk in to that welcoming, book-lined foyer. The staff is excellent, the books are enticing, and the hotel's small size keeps things cozy amidst the enormity of the city outside its doors.

And the mid-town location? What's not to like? Perfect.

The ample scaffolding that encases the building tells me something is being repaired on the exterior. If that's correct, then I am all for fixing what's broken.

But my reason for four stars rather than five is this: the interior of the hotel is in need of a refresh. I hope the chain addresses that soon so that the place retains its stellar reputation.
