Unfortunately, our stay at the resort was quite disappointing. The facilities were extremely dated and in need of refurbishment. The layout felt overly compact—amenities like the pool, water slides, playground, and rooms were all tightly clustered together, which made the environment feel crowded and far from relaxing.

Noise was a major issue. The walls were very thin, and we could hear everything from the neighboring rooms. Additionally, all the rooms faced either the main road or the pool area, both of which were consistently loud, making it hard to unwind.

Cleanliness also left much to be desired. Our toilet had an unpleasant odor despite being "cleaned" daily, and there were visible smudges around it. The lobby had a strong, unpleasant scent reminiscent of a daycare—unfortunately, not in a comforting way.

The on-site dining options were underwhelming. The food was basic and generally poor in quality. Although the resort advertises a wide range of kids’ activities, they were often booked out quickly, making it hard to participate—especially if visiting with a group.

The kids’ club was located in a dim, underground space with very limited natural light or outdoor access, which felt uninspiring and uninviting for children.

If it weren’t for the fact that we were staying with friends, we would have checked out early and looked for alternative accommodation—it was that disappointing.
